body:
*@imReker commented on Jan 27, 2021, 1:30 PM UTC:*

## Steps to Reproduce

1.  Run app.
2.  Click "Flutter attach" button.
3.  Stop app.
4.  Set a valid "Build flavor" in "Run/Debug Configurations" window, eg, "MyFlavor".
5.  Run app.
6.  Click "Flutter attach" button.
7.  Open "Run/Debug Configurations" window, check the configurations and close the window.
8.  Click "Flutter attach" button.
9.  Open "Run/Debug Configurations" window.

After Step 2, debugger attached to app successfully.

After Step 6, attach failed and Debug Console print: "Could not find an option named "flavor".

After Setp 7, "Additional arguments" became from empty to "--flavor=MyFlavor".

After Setp 9, "Additional arguments" became to "--flavor=MyFlavor --flavor=MyFlavor".

**Related:** [#4521](https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/issues/4521)

[![screenshot](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4949937/105997608-c643aa80-60e6-11eb-9f0c-eb6f8c245ae3.png)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4949937/105997608-c643aa80-60e6-11eb-9f0c-eb6f8c245ae3.png)

## Version info

Flutter: 1.26.0-2.0.pre.137 • channel master •
Flutter plugin: 52.2.1 in Intellij Marketplace.

*This issue was moved by [stevemessick](https://github.com/stevemessick) from [flutter/flutter-intellij#5217](https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/issues/5217).*

comment_data.body:
*@stevemessick commented on Jan 29, 2021, 3:56 PM UTC:*

`flutter attach` does not have a `--flavor` option.

Hi @imReker
You're trying to use a command that doesn't exist, it's not a bug. 
Can you please provide more details on why you need to use this? and provide some use cases.
Note: you can use flavors to build
Thank you

@TahaTesser 

I'm NOT using a command that doesn't exist, I didn't use any command, what I'm doing is:
A. Set "Build flavor" in "Run/Debug Configurations" and Run app.
B. Click attach button to attach to the running app without changing "Run/Debug Configurations".
A and B are done in Intellij GUI. And when I combine A and B, bug appeared. I can not attach to the app, because the "attach button" will pass the unsupported "flavor" param to command line, or, "flutter attach" command will not ignore the "flavor" param set by Intellij.

Every time I want to attach a running app with flavor, I need to change "Run/Debug Configurations" first, and if I want just running app, I need to change back, it's very strange.
**There are many other people bothered by this bug, see: https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/issues/4521**

And, if I re-do step 9 more times, eg, click 5 times, the "Additional arguments" would become to "--flavor=MyFlavor --flavor=MyFlavor --flavor=MyFlavor --flavor=MyFlavor --flavor=MyFlavor". The attach button unexpectedly changed my "Run/Debug Configurations".

@TahaTesser 
I think this bug is produced by Intellij Plugin, not flutter command, but as you see, the admin of flutter/flutter-intellij moved the issue to here.

@TahaTesser Could you change the title to: 'flutter attach' should not
include the --flavor parameter
Then move this back to flutter/flutter-intellij, please?
Thanks!
